article.headline: W. Michigan 80, E. Michigan 61
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Shawntes Gary scored 16 points and Derek Drews added 15, helping Western Michigan rally for an 80-61 victory over Eastern Michigan on Thursday night. Trailing 32-26 at halftime, the Broncos (13-14, 7-6 Mid American) opened the second half with a 24-7 run and coasted to their ninth straight win over the Eagles (10-17, 4-9). Michael Redell scored 12 points, Andre Ricks had 11 off the bench and Joe Reitz added 10 for Western, which shot 69.6 percent (16-for-23) in the second half and 55 percent for the game. Eastern Michigan's Travis Lewis had 11 points and a game-high 10 rebounds. Jesse Bunkley also scored 11 points and Jarred Axon and James Matthews had 10 apiece.
